<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Melee characters on the PvP server</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Angus[CC]">Angus[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:40 a.m. 5/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Melee characters on the PvP server<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1269" TARGET=_self>Re: Melee characters on the PvP server</A> (jaeger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Actually if the tank can take the brunt of the magic class's

<BR>&gt; mana he can usually win.. Even though he's hurt, especially
<BR>&gt; monks with their mend skill. Once it goes down to actually melee
<BR>&gt; I'd take the pure fighting class over the hybrid.. Plus if he
<BR>&gt; can do enough damage while your casting.. ie disrupt spells and
<BR>&gt; hit of a bit of damage it just makes it easier.. Don't get me
<BR>&gt; wrong though, magic class's do kick ass and will probably win
<BR>&gt; most times but it the hands of a skilled player a melee class
<BR>&gt; could win.
<P>&gt; I was thinking just now, rogues.. Magic class's have to stop to
<BR>&gt; cast.. Backstab.. That would be a pretty powerful in a duel.
<BR>&gt; Probably would freak the mage out, being hit for 40+ points of
<BR>&gt; damage kinda does that to you. of course, I don't have a level
<BR>&gt; 10 rogue yet so I can't check that out.
<P>FYI: Rogues are decent melee class fighters, but back stab is very hard to use solo. You would really only be able to employ it during group fights. I have not tested backstab lately but I did have a level 10 rogue and the backstab was not worth anything at that level. At later levels say around level 30-35 it really starts dealing out the damage.
<P>The point of my post was to once again encourage people to look at the picture instaed of just wahta duels the best. Dueling is totally lame to me, way to one sided for some classes. But I will tell you this your in real touble leveling without melee classes to back you up at later levels. Just a warning.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
